                            <comment id="13479375" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 21:21:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One a related note:&lt;br/&gt;
It is difficult for user to find out the correlation between region name and scanner name when they see:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Caused by: org.apache.hadoop.hbase.UnknownScannerException: org.apache.hadoop.hbase.UnknownScannerException: Name: -3944363018500584369
	at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.HRegionServer.next(HRegionServer.java:1869)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When entry keyed by scannerName is removed from scanners map, can we temporarily store (scanner name, region name) mapping so that the above exception message can provide more information to the user ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13479486" author="stack" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 23:42:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes.  In general scannerid is opaque.  Would be good to return something more informative.  I see the same issue when we get the TooSlow messages in the log.  Its logging scannerid which tells us next to nothing.. so some means of logging scannerid plus current row or at least current region would be of more use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13621605" author="stack" created="Thu, 4 Apr 2013 00:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving unowned feature out of 0.95 (though this would be a good one to have).  Helps w/ usability.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
